metadata.name: blub blub #37
metadata.description:
blub blub is an exploration of form.

We begin with two simple shapes, one defining the shape that will be drawn, the other defining the path along which it will traverse.

Each shape is then paired with a sinusoid that either modifies the size of the shape that is drawn, or the offset from the path it is traversing.

This simple set of rules leads to a surprising large variety of forms.

metadata.name: Treasured Rug #15
metadata.description:
A form of concrete poetry depicting a rug.
Typography created by multiple lines of typewriter text.
Features one of five possible character sets.
One of ten possible palettes for text color
90% chance of black paper, or 10% chance of white
10% chance of rare "Wild" character shift, otherwise 45% of either "Loose" or "Tight"
15% chance each of either rare "Narrow" or "Wide" rug otherwise "Standard"
3 styles of paper grain
Differing line gaps
Differing types of skew effect
Differing types of blend effect when characters overlay.

Press S to save in High Resolution

Uses p5.js and scribble.js
@p1x3lboy August 2022

metadata.name: TRQ.1 #11
metadata.description:
The aesthetics of the work is inspired by the work of the Brazilian artist DIONISIO DEL SANTO, above all, the formal simplification, the use of geometric figures, in addition to planes and colors, in a simplified way, the work also makes reference to the principles of Concretism, as a movement artistic.

Features:
PALETTES
In total, the work has fifteen different color palettes, with percentages of probability of occurrence varying between 2% and 15%.

FORMES
The images are structured using only three simple shapes (square, rectangle and triangle) proportional to each other. Said shapes can also be rotated and interleaved with empty squares.
The use of each one of the forms follows three different combination patterns, according to the description and percentages of occurrence indicated below:
‚Äú+++‚Äù ‚Äì 50% | full square + triangle
‚Äú++‚Äù ‚Äì 35% | rectangle + triangle
‚Äú+‚Äù ‚Äì 15% | just triangle

INVERS√â
One of the rare features, with only a 10% probability, is the occurrence of the inverted color palette, in which the colors of the background, simple shapes and frame, are put in negative.

VECTEUR
The background was structured following two possible direction vectors (horizontal ‚Äì 40% or vertical ‚Äì 60%).

MODULES
The canvas can be subdivided following three different modulations, which can be 3X3 (20% chance), 4X4 (45% chance) or 5X5 (35% chance).

September 01, 2022.
Generative token by Paivei made with p5js for FxHash.

metadata.name: NO ROADMAP #235
metadata.description:
This collection represents the need we have to move forward despite the obstacles that the road may present us.
We identify ourselves with the one who, even without the most optimal conditions, continues on its way until the goal is reached
Web 3.0 is a space that appears to us without a roadmap, so that everyone can explore it and learn.
Even though we only get to have a skateboard, in this journey of work and effort, we will continue asking ourselves until we can at last get it
WEN LAMBO?

+ 50 Backgrounds + Color variations
+ 30 Foreground
+ 50 Animals
+ 25 Foreground elements
+ 10 Police cars on fire

metadata.name: Kintsugi Pottery #33
metadata.description:
Kintsugi Pottery
Copyright 2022 Jeff Clark

Broken can be beautiful. Flaws, imperfection, signs of age and wear add character and give a sense of history.

It's true of pottery and it's true of many other things.

Kintsugi is the Japanese art of repairing broken pottery by mending the areas of breakage with lacquer dusted or mixed with powdered gold, silver, or platinum. (Wikipedia)

This 100% generative system creates pottery designs inspired by the philosophy of Kintsugi. All the bowls are cracked and repaired with gold. Some have small engraved messages. Colors and bowl shapes are not necessarily based on traditional Japanese designs. Color and vessel shape vary greatly.

Features:
Type - Square, Hexagonal, Octagonal, Decagonal, Round
Tilt - number (3-14)
Assymetry - Left, None, Right
Ring Striping - true, false
Vertical Striping - true, false
Message - true, false
Lumpiness - None, Low, Medium, High

metadata.name: Flimsy #6
metadata.description:
This started as an abstract project but the output gradually came to resemble some creatures of the sea like jellyfish and sea slugs. I decided this time to go with the flow and added spines and eye spots to make them look a bit more organic.

Initially this will be a free mint as a reward to the holders of my existing projects. After a day or so the reserves will be removed and the remainder will be available to anyone for a small amount of tezos.

Primary Features:
Layout - Open 40%, Closed 40%, U-Shaped 15%, Radial 5%
Background - Spots 50%, Lines 50%
Spines - true 25%, false 75%
EyeSpots - true 25%, false 75%
Ridges - true 25%, false 75%
Marking - Bands 50%, Stripes 50%

Copyright 2022 Jeff Clark
